Head of Dr. Fritsch (1917)

The original poem "I, eternal child" by Egon Schiele. This is Egon's own handwriting, which got him a job as a clerk in a POW camp near the town of Mühling. There, he was allowed to draw and paint imprisoned Russian officers; his commander, Karl Moser (who assumed that Schiele was a painter and decorator when he first met him), even gave him a disused store room to use as a studio. • 
Ich, ewiges Kind, Egon Schiele
•
#poetry #poems #poemoftheday #egonschieleofficial #egonschiele #schiele #artistsoninstagram #artistsofinstagram #artistry #masterofart #expressionism

I, eternal child -
I sacrificed myself for others
who looked and did not see me

Everything was dear to me-
I wanted to look at the angry people
with loving eyes,
to make their eyes do likewise;
And to the jealous, 
give them gifts,
telling them I am worthless.'
-"I, eternal child", poetry by Egon Schiele

It's amazing that when you know an artist well, you're able to tell it's their painting even if you've never seen it before. There's something dinstinct about Schiele's landscapes that sort of give you the same feeling that his portraits give. It's that special spirit and style put into art, that makes a great artist.
